# Commit Message Template
# 
# Follow the conventional commit format:
# <type>(<scope>): <description>
#
# Types:
#   feat     - New feature
#   fix      - Bug fix
#   docs     - Documentation changes
#   style    - Code style changes (formatting, etc.)
#   refactor - Code refactoring
#   test     - Adding or updating tests
#   chore    - Maintenance tasks
#
# Scope (optional):
#   - Use lowercase
#   - No spaces
#   - Examples: equibind, gnina, vina, api, ui, docker
#
# Description:
#   - Use imperative mood ("add" not "added")
#   - Max 72 characters
#   - No period at the end
#
# Examples:
#   feat(equibind): add model integration
#   fix(gnina): resolve memory leak in batch processing
#   docs(api): update API documentation
#   test(vina): add unit tests for docking engine
#   chore(docker): update base image version

<type>(<scope>): <description>

# Optional: Add a longer description after a blank line
# 
# - Bullet points for details
# - Explain why the change was made
# - Reference related issues

# Optional: Add footer for issue references
# 
# Closes #123
# Fixes #456
# Related to #789 